  <discussion>Herzogiella seligeri is distinguished by the wide-spreading leaves that appear in several rows and the long (2–3.5 mm), arcuate capsules. The species occurs in the flora area only in northwestern North America west of the Rocky Mountains at elevations usually below 900 m.</discussion>
